

class Solution {
    public ArrayList<Integer> findDuplicates(int[] arr) {
        
        int n = arr.length;			                                            	// get array length
        Arrays.sort(arr);			                                            	// sort the array (O(n log n))
        
        ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();	                    // store duplicates
        
        for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++){			                                      // traverse till second last element
            if(arr[i] == arr[i+1]){		                                    // check adjacent equal elements
                list.add(arr[i]);		                                      // add duplicate to list
            }
        }
        return list;				                                              // return duplicate elements
    }
}

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Array Duplicates:
Given an array arr[] of size n, containing elements from the range 1 to n, and each element appears at most twice, return an array of all the integers that appears twice.

Note: You can return the elements in any order but the driver code will print them in sorted order.

Examples:

Input: arr[] = [2, 3, 1, 2, 3]
Output: [2, 3] 
Explanation: 2 and 3 occur more than once in the given array.

Input: arr[] = [3, 1, 2] 
Output: []
Explanation: There is no repeating element in the array, so the output is empty.

Constraints:
1 ≤ n ≤ 106
1 ≤ arr[i] ≤ n

